This is  not really  possible, since some  programs want  control over
their settings. I have received  quite a number of complaints that you
cannot disable dithering  in Heretic II - this is  of course caused by
the Warp3D/Permedia2/dither variable, which indeed *is* global...

> "QUEUESIZE": What is the best value for that variable (e.g. for QuakeGL=
 or
> Heretic2) ?

QUEUESIZE  is for  indirect render  contexts only.  It  was originally
invented to work  around the problem that you  have to Lock/Unlock the
hardware, which  is hard to  do if you're  doing OpenGL. It  has shown
that using  timer-based locking, as  done in StormMesa and  MiniGL, is
far better performance-wise.=20

The stuff is still in for historical/compatibility reasons, but should
be considered deprecated and not used anymore.=20

Best regards. Hans-Joerg.

