On 9 Jun 2000, Dan Plant wrote:
> in LIBS:. I think they were part of the RTG Master package that I've
> never used. Anyway they are gone now and it's 3D all the way. The
> libraries concerned were:
>    rtg.library

rtg.library is not an rtgmaster lib. I don't know where it comes from...

Here's the catch: When the W3D_CyberGfx.library starts up, it opens
cybergraphics.library. "Unfortunately", P96 mimics the API of CGX, so
there's no way of telling if it's CGX, or P96 spoofing to be CGX.

OTOH, opening Picasso96API.library may open the emulation library (I think
it was written by Steffen Haeuser), so the only safe possibility is to
open some of the internal P96 libs, in our case it's rtg.library, which is
only loaded if P96 is actually active.

Unfortunately, there's this old rtg.library, and at the time of writing
the driver, we've never heard of that. It was just at a later point when
somebody actually had this problem that we became aware of that.

Sorry for the inconvenience that may have caused.

