Hi,

On Mon, 19 Jun 2000, Alan Buxey wrote:
> > available. But they are not. And when you look how permedia2 already
> > limits heretic2, what will be with the other games? 
> 
> I've been doing some calculations...and, if the bandwidth isnt currently a
> limit , but the fill-rate of the PermediaII *is*, then this Mediator board
> with its 4-6Mb faster BUS and a voodoo3 gfx card will achieve 3-4x the
> framerate of current games (on a 604e) - with 2-3x faster on a 603e

Remember you'll also be able to play at higher resolutions. 1024x768 isn't
really a problem for the Voodoo 3 anymore.

Also, remember that H2 uses lightmaps. This means that every polygon is
rendered twice. If you have blast marks on the walls, it's even rendered a
third time. With a Voodoo 3, this is going to be a lot better. It supports
multitexturing, which means that the actual polygon is only rendered once.
This reduces bus traffic. Plus, it has a larger memory, so texture
swapping will also be reduced.

Concerning other games, H2 is really a very heavy load for the Amiga.
Shogo can, for example, use vertex lighting instead of lightmaps (you can
disable it on the fly), so if lightmaps are too slow, you go for vertex
lighting (not the same visual quality, but faster). Also, Shogo can reduce
the model complexity. It uses Level-of-Detail for the models, so that
models that are far away are only rendered with a few polygons. It's
possible to scale that range, so the reduction is done earlier, which
increases speed a lot...

