There's an env variable named "Dither". If set, dithering is always
enabled. If 0, you can turn it on or off in Heretic 2 by setting
gl_dither to 1 or zero to turn dithering on and off, respectively. The
"pixelated" look may also come from disabling the filter mode. The H2
console variable gl_texturemode can be set to either "GL_LINEAR", for
linear filtering, or "GL_NEAREST", to turn it of. It looks nicer with
GL_LINEAR, of course.

