You have to specify "-cddir dhx:HereticII" in the starter GUI in order
to have the videos played from disk. 

> 3) Every time I start H2 the standard videoformat is 640x480. Is it possible
>    too use another format right after start, or do I have to change it every
>    time when starting?

The video mode should be stored in the "config.cfg" file in your user/
dir in the shape of a  "set vid_mode n", where n=0,1,2... Usually 0 is
320x240, 1  is 400x300, 2 is  512x384 and 4 is  640x480 (it continues,
but the P2 cannot really cope with H2 at anything higher :-)

The config.cfg  file is written when  you quit the  program. Make sure
that everything is write enabled. 

If  everything else  fails, put  a  file "autoexec.cfg"  in your  user
directory, which can be executed at  startup. In this file you can put
something like

-- SNIP --
// autoexec.cfg
// correct crash problems when jumping into water
set r_fog_mode 0
// set resultion
set vid_mode 0
-- SNIP --

The first  "set" command fixes  the problems people  have experiencing
when jumping into the water. The second "set" sets the video mode. But
this variable should definately be set when the program exits...

