Nothing  spectacular  really,  it   just  means  that  the  extensions
mentioned are  not provided by  the MiniGL. WGL_EXT_swap_control  is a
windows addition anyway. point_parameters  I think can be used instead
of  a  texture  for  particles. the  shared_texturepalettes  extension
allows you  to upload 8 bit  paletted textures with  a common palette,
but since  neither driver for Warp3D  supports them, it's  no in there
either.  The last  two are  different extensions  for the  same thing,
multitexturing,  but since there  is no  hardware (yet)  that supports
that, it's not in it either. 

The Quake2 engine can run without them, there are just "bonuses" added
(yeah I know  it's not bonuses)... I had a  Mesa renderer running that
did provide them but didn't prove to be visually more attractive, only
half as fast :)

